<PRE># Apache NiFi on Kubernetes=0A=
=0A=
## Install Kubernetes=0A=
=0A=
* Install kubernetes using minikube=0A=
=0A=
        brew install minikube=0A=
 =0A=
* Start minikube=0A=
 =0A=
        minikube start --memory=3D4096=0A=
               =0A=
* Mount folder to minikube, so that pods can have access to local storage=0A=
        =0A=
        minikube mount &lt;src-dir&gt;:/&lt;dst-dir&gt;=0A=
=0A=
* Let K8s use local docker env=0A=
=0A=
        eval $(minikube docker-env)=0A=
                                  =0A=
* Create default memory limits=0A=
=0A=
        kubectl create -f memory-defaults.yaml=0A=
        =0A=
* Create Apache NiFi Deployment=0A=
=0A=
        kubectl create -f nifi.yaml=0A=
        =0A=
* Create Apache NiFi Service=0A=
=0A=
        kubectl create -f nifi-svc.yaml=0A=
=0A=
* Run the following command to open Apache NiFi dashboard=0A=
=0A=
        minikube service flow-4                </PRE></BODY></HTML>
